    "name": "CANDEO HOTELS Fukuoka Tenjin",
    "detail": "Excellent hotel that looks a lot more slick than what you pay for. Compared to other Fukuoka hotels, this had a good location, centrally placed between nakasu and tenjin. Rooms were clean with nice enough facilities. Staff were friendly, courteous and unobtrusive. The best part was the frankly lovely roof spa that was open all night and free for guests. Having a soak in the roof onsen in the open air after a night on the tiles was amazing. The only slight quibble I had was with the jammed elevators, only two to service the whole building, with the lobby placed on the 9th floor bizarrely. All in all though, I would definitely stay again. ",
